<br>
Here are the facts:<br>
Speed of Light ~ 300,000 km/sec<br>
Typical round trip packet travel time ~ 250-300msec (540msec for early satellite communication).<br>
<br>
With Low Orbit satellites the propogation delay will be reduced, but no where near 3msec.<br>
<br>
Fact of the matter, unless you live where there is no telephone or cable and the weather is always sunny, satellite will not produce an enjoyable gaming experience.<br>
<br>
/em wipes the rest of the dust off the book and puts it back on the shelf. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=80051" target="_blank">Ryft</a>
<Br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uulvrim.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ulvrim</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Been around a while</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(4/9/02 11:19:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2173.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> about latency</span><hr size=1> just fyi we swedish d00ds have a ping around 700ms most of the time, sometimes on off-hours its a bit lower, around 400 and on raids I go up to between 1000-4000 ms. I can still play without whining :P. Its not as if EQ is very ping dependant like Quake or something, but sure, satellite-link is probably even slower, and for all you ninja-looters out there all this latency will cause problems.<br>
<br>
