 <p>Mirdorr, 28 bard, Ayonae Ro
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uannakakornacopia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Annaka Kornacopia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>New to the block</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(4/12/02 1:03:28 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2173.topic&index=29>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.trogg.net/ECC/Pics/Anna.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: about latency</span><hr size=1> Congrats Carabella on getting your cable company to &quot;fix&quot; your cable modem.<br>
<br>
I have been using DirecPC, one-way satelite for 7 years now, do to I live in the sticks. No DSL, no cable, just regular dial-up. LOL, started out paying $120/mo for unlimited, just glad they lowered it to $40/mo after DSL and Cable became more availible to people.<br>
<br>
In my experience, there is an 8 second delay from the time I send the request and recieve the information.  This is a great boon to me for surfing the web and downloading driver updates, files, pics, etc.  But 8 secs in EQ is instant death.<br>
 <br>
 <p><img src=http://www.trogg.net/ECC/annabanner1.jpg><BR><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=84965>Annaka Kornacopia's Profile</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ubriscoecounty.showPublicProfile?language=EN>BriscoeCounty</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>New to the block</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(4/16/02 11:13:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2173.topic&index=30>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Satellite internet</span><hr size=1> I used Starband when I started EQ and all the way up to around level 15 with my Ranger.  Once the game actually started to require some skill I started playing on dial up...satellite didn't cut it.<br>
I still use the satellite to download big patches or just to log in when I want to move my character to a different zone or do trading.<br>
I would never be able to solo with the satellite link, and if I could group with it it would just mean that the group didn't really need me all that badly <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uedywenubergeek.showPublicProfile?language=EN>EdywenUbergeek</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Been around a while</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(4/18/02 9:50:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2173.topic&index=31>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> re: Sat Internet</span><hr size=1> At present, the 2 Sat providers, have a 700ms min round trip time, 350 to base station, and 350 back. I tested this while I was employed for a security company testing sat securtiy products. This does not take into account bad weather, numerous base station downtimes (granted its still a new consumer technology, using relatively cheap hardware, compared to the commercial sat equipment  which use $100k's worth of equipment).<br>
<br>
Basically, you get hit with the 700ms everytime a new packet is created and bounced, for games its useless, for web its almost useless as you create a new socket for each and every image you sucks down.  For ftp where an initial connect is made and then a stream of packets are sent, its fine, although your initial get statement will be 700ms behind, once it gets going its fast.<br>
<br>
Edy <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showMessageRange?topicID=2173.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a> <b>2</b>  </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showPrevMessage?topicID=2173.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showNextMessage?topicID=2173.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2173.topic&index=31><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/grunge/addReply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.emailToFriend?topicID=2173.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.threadControl?topicID=2173.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/grunge/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=2173.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=2173.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub42.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="ayonaerofrm1">General Forum<option value="ayonaerofrm6">NAG (Nearly Anything Goes)<option value="ayonaerofrm7">The Bazaar<option value="ayonaerofrm12">Nuggets<option value="ayonaerofrm8">Raid Forum<option v